Our Client: Allison Cundiff
Date of Loss: April 6, 2021
Location: 1100 West Hollywood Ave.                                       I am requesting an opportunity to inspect or obtain copies of public records and
any and all documents, records, and things relating to the
construction/roadwork, lane closure, and lane control being performed on April
6, 2021 at or around 1100 West Hollywood Avenue in Chicago, IL (the “Work”),
including but not limited to the following:
 contracts, agreements, contract documents, bid documents, estimates, and
contract information (book);
 plans, special provisions, specifications, and requirements;
 type, scope, and nature of work being performed;
 beginning and completion dates for work being performed;
 work zone safety manual;
 work zone traffic control and direction activities;
 policies and procedures for road closures (full or partial) and lane closures
(full or partial);
 correspondence, SMS/text messages, and e‐mails;
 invoices, orders, purchase, and receipts;
 payroll records, timesheets, logs, and daily work logs;
 photographs, video, digital imagery, or the like of the Work;
 photographs, video, digital imagery, or the like showing the vehicles and
persons involved in the collision on April 6, 2021 at or near the location of
the Work at or around 9:00 a.m.;
 and a list of names and contact information for any and all
parties/witnesses.

Any and all policies, instructions, memos, manuals, rulebooks, training materials, guidelines, or emails since January 1, 2009 pertaining to FOIA procedures.  Examples of records include: 
(a) documents (e.g. manuals, guidelines, rulebooks, training materials, etc.) that guide FOIA officers on how to receive, interpret, identify, search, or process requests or appeals;

(b) internal memos and/or emails with updates, changes, or reminders about FOIA compliance policies or procedures;

(c) materials with case studies, scenarios, or other information used for training, teaching, or guiding FOIA officers;    

(d) statistics about the number of requests received, processed, complied with, appealed, and overturned;

(e) any documents (e.g. memos, guidelines, emails, lists, databases, spreadsheets, etc.) pertaining to handling or processing submissions from (i) specific individuals, organizations, or companies or (ii) types or categories of actors and entities.   

For records that are in electronic format, I request the information be furnished in the electronic format in which it is maintained.  If the information is maintained in custom electronic format not currently available to the public, I request the information be furnished in an electronic format that is viewable by standard software, such as Excel.  Please furnish all electronic documents to the email address listed above.

